%N A395354 Consider the spiral of red and black knights shown in A392177 and A392178. If the n-th square along the non-negative x-axis contains a black knight then a(n) = n, if it contains a red knight then a(n) = -n, otherwise a(n) = 0.
%C A395354 This is the analog of A395353 for the positive x-axis.
%C A395354 [Needs a much bigger b-file, in order to see if those runs of zeros are going to persist]
%H A395354 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A395354/b395354.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..150</a>
%Y A395354 Cf. A392177, A392178, A395353.
%K A395354 sign,new
%O A395354 0,3
